)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@       PSUDOP            . DEFINE OPCODES OF APLYJ
)@@G@@ MACHINE    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@/. CODE IS STORED IN THE LARGEST FREE BLOCYK
)@@G@@K IN THE WS, IN FULL WORDS.   @G@@@@.  THE RIGHT HALF IS THE OPCODE, THEYL
)@@G@@ LEFT IS THE SEQUENCE NO (IN THE    @F@@@@.  LEXICAL TEXT) OF THE ITEM WYM
)@@G@@HICH GENERATED THIS WORD (FOR USER  @F@@@@.  DIAGNOSTICS).  SINCE DATA SYN
)@@G@@TORAGE IS ALLOCATED FROM THE LEFT   @G@@@@.  (LOW ADDRESSES) OF FREE BLOYO
)@@G@@X, WE ATTEMPT TO MINIMIZE FRAGMENTATION   @G@@@@.  BY ALLOCATING CODE SPYP
)@@G@@ACE FROM THE RIGHT.  THUS CODE GENERATED BY     @G@@@@.  THE LEFT SIDE OYQ
)@@G@@F A STATEMENT APPEARS ON THE RIGHT SIDE OF A CODE     @F@@@@.  BLOK, ANDYR
)@@G@@ R-TO-L EXECUTION OF A STMNT IS L-TO-R SCANNING OF THE@]@@@@.  C-STRING.YS
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@       INSTRS .   @B@@@@. INITIALIZE-- GET BLOCK, SET YT
)@@G@@REGS, ETC...@ @@@@CODSTO* SX   X11,CSLINK  .    @E@@@@       UNLNKL     YU
)@@G@@       . FIND AND UNLINK LARGEST BLOCK    @D@@@@       LA    A0,WSFLWA  YV
)@@G@@ . RHGHT HAND WORD OF BLOCK   @ @@@@       ABSADR A0         .    @F@@@@YW
)@@G@@       LX,U  X7,0,A0     . MAKE IT 1ST WORD TO BE STORED INTO     @D@@@@YX
)@@G@@       AA,U  A0,1        . BUMP FOR LATER SUBTRACTIONS@E@@@@       SA   YY
)@@G@@ A0,CSFLWA   . AND SAVE ABS ADDR OF LAST WD + 1 @G@@@@       LXI,U X7,07YZ
)@@G@@77776  . SET STEP MINUS 1 FOR LEFT TO RIGHT STORING   @F@@@@       LA   ZA
)@@G@@ A0,WSFFWA   . ADDR OF LEFTMOST WD IN POOLED BLOCK    @ @@@@       ABSADZB
)@@G@@R A0         .    @C@@@@       SA    A0,CSFFWA   . SAVE FOR WSFULL TESTSZC
)@@G@@@D@@@@       LX,U  X6,CS0100   . SET POINTER TO STORE RTNE  @ @@@@      ZD
)@@G@@ LX    X11,CSLINK  .    @B@@@@       J     1,X11       . NORMAL EXIT    ZE
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. AFTER INITIALIZATION, TEXT IN A0 IS STORED BY LMJ X6ZF
)@@G@@,0,X6 TO HERE---  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@CS0100 LA,U  A1,0,X7     . ADDR OF TZG
)@@G@@ARGET WORD  @B@@@@       TLE   A1,CSFFWA   . WITHIN LIMITS? @C@@@@      ZH
)@@G@@ J     CS0110      . NO, TAKE WSFULL EXIT @B@@@@       SA    A0,0,*X7   ZI
)@@G@@ . YES, STASH DATA@B@@@@       LMJ   X6,1,X6     . AND RETURN     @ @@@@ZJ
)@@G@@       J     CS0100      .    @ @@@@CS0110 ERROR YWSFUL      .    @ @@@@ZK
)@@G@@       J     0,X6        .    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. GENERATE HALFWORD ADDRZL
)@@G@@-- USED BY COMPILER FOR HISTORICAL REASONS@[@@@@.     @C@@@@CODHWA* LA,UZM
)@@G@@ A1,0,X7     . ADDR OF NEXT WORD    @A@@@@       TLE   A1,CSFFWA   . IN ZN
)@@G@@RANGE?@B@@@@       J     CH0100      . NO, WSFULL.    @ @@@@       RELADZO
)@@G@@R A1         .    @A@@@@       J     1,X11       . AND QUIT @ @@@@CH0100ZP
)@@G@@ ERROR YWSFUL      .    @ @@@@       J     0,X11       .    @ @@@@. ABORZQ
)@@G@@T STORAGE OF C-STRING   @ @@@@CODABT* SX   X11,CSLINK  .    @D@@@@      ZR
)@@G@@ LA    A1,WSDBUG   . GET DEBUGGING CONTROL FLAG @G@@@@       JOP,U A1,4 ZS
)@@G@@CC0005 . IF ERASING IS INHIBITED, JUST CLOSE THE BLOCK@C@@@@       LA   ZT
)@@G@@ A0,CSFLWA   . ABSADR OF LAST WORD+1@G@@@@       ANA   A0,CSFFWA   . LESZU
)@@G@@S ABSADR OF 1ST WD GIVES NO OF WDS TO FREE@C@@@@       LA    A1,WSFFWA  ZV
)@@G@@ . RELADR OF 1ST WD     @D@@@@       FREE              . PUT BACK ONTO FZW
)@@G@@REE LIST    @C@@@@       J     CC0010      . GO TAKE NORMAL EXIT  @[@@@@ZX
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. CLOSE OUT STORAGE OF C-STRING.  LEAVES RELADR OF BLOK IN AZY
)@@G@@0     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@CODCLO* SX   X11,CSLINK  .    @G@@@@CC0005 LA,U ZZ
)@@G@@ A0,0,X7     . ADDR OF NEXT WORD (WHERE HEADER WILL GO)     @G@@@@      AA
)@@G@@ ANA   A0,CSFFWA   . LESS ABSADR OF 1ST WD=NO OF UNUSED WORDS     @F@@@@AB
)@@G@@       JG,U  A0,2 CC0100 . WSFULL UNLESS AT LEAST 2 WORDS ARE LEFT@E@@@@AC
)@@G@@       LA    A1,WSFFWA   . PICK UP RELADR OF START OF BLOCK @C@@@@      AD
)@@G@@ FREE              . RELEASE UNUSED SPACE @E@@@@       LA    A0,CSFLWA  AE
)@@G@@ . ABSADR OF LAST WORD IN BLOK +1   @G@@@@       ANA,U A0,0,X7     . LESAF
)@@G@@S ADDR OF 1ST WORD USED=NO OF WDS USED    @F@@@@       AA    A0,(+ZTPCODAG
)@@G@@,0,0,0,0,0) . PLUG IN SKELETON HEADER     @F@@@@       SA    A0,0,X7    AH
)@@G@@ . PUT HDR WD INTO LEFT MOST WORD OFBLOCK @D@@@@       LA,U  A0,0,X7    AI
)@@G@@ . GET ADDR OF BLOCK HDR WORD @ @@@@       RELADR A0         .    @ @@@@AJ
)@@G@@CC0010 LX    X11,CSLINK  .    @C@@@@       SZ    WSFFWA      . CLEAR SPLAK
)@@G@@ITBOLK FLAGS@ @@@@       SZ    WSFLWA      .    @ @@@@       J     1,X11AL
)@@G@@       .    @ @@@@CC0100 ERROR YWSFUL      .    @ @@@@       LX,H2 X11,CAM
)@@G@@SLINK  .    @ @@@@       J     0,X11       .    @D@@@@. ERASE A BLOCK OFAN
)@@G@@ COMPILED CODE (A0=RELADR OF BLOCK) @ @@@@CODERS* SX   X11,CSLINK  .    AO
)@@G@@@D@@@@       LA    A1,WSDBUG   . GET DEBUGGING CONTROL FLAG @E@@@@      AP
)@@G@@ JOP,U A1,4 1,X11  . AND EXIT IF ERASING IS INHIBITED @E@@@@       LA   AQ
)@@G@@ A1,A0       . SET UP BLOCK RELADR FOR ERASE    @ @@@@       ABSADR A0  AR
)@@G@@       .    @B@@@@       LA,S1 A2,0,A0     . GET BLOCKTYPE  @D@@@@      AS
)@@G@@ TE,U  A2,ZTPCOD   . IS IT REALLY A CODE BLOCK? @B@@@@       ER    ERR$ AT
)@@G@@       . NO, CRASH!     @C@@@@       LA,H2 A0,0,A0     . YES, GET ITS LEAU
)@@G@@NGTH  @C@@@@       FREE              . RELEASE THE SPACE    @ @@@@      AV
)@@G@@ LX,H2 X11,CSLINK  .    @B@@@@       J     1,X11       . NORMAL EXIT    AW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@       VARBLS            .    @ @@@@CSLINK RES   1    AX
)@@G@@       .    @ @@@@CSFFWA RES   1           .    @ @@@@CSFLWA RES   1    AY
)@@G@@       .    @]@@@@       END .___@@@       J     CH0100      . NO, WSFULAZ
)@@G@@L.    @ @@@@       RELADR A1         .    @A@@@@       J     1,X11      BA
)@@G@@ . AND QUIT @ @@@@CH0100 ERROR YWSFUL      .    *[S@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@. ****BB
)@@G@@***************************************************************** @G@@@@BC
)@@G@@. STANDARD PROCS - INCLUDED BY AN @ADD PRCPKG/APL IN SOURCE DECKS     * BD
)@@G@@@G@@@@.                                                                 BE
)@@G@@    * @^@@@@       AXR$         .   @C@@@@       CONFIG  .    DEFINE ASSBF
)@@G@@EMBLY PARAMETERS  @G@@@@       APSYMB.     DEFINE APL SYMBOL SET        BG
)@@G@@                      * @G@@@@       WSDEF.      DEFINE WORKSPACE       BH
)@@G@@                            * @G@@@@WORKSP INFO  2 20.      SET ASIDE THBI
)@@G@@E SPACE                           * @G@@@@       RUNCTL.     DEFINE RUN BJ
)@@G@@CTRL BLOK(S)                            * @G@@@@RUNCON INFO  2 22.      BK
)@@G@@AND SET ASIDE ITS  SPACE                      * @G@@@@       CBLOCK     BL
)@@G@@       . DEFINE CONTROL BLOCK TYPES                 * @G@@@@.           BM
)@@G@@                                                          * @G@@@@. END BN
)@@G@@OF STANDARD PROC BLOCK                                          * @G@@@@BO
)@@G@@. ********************************************************************* BP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. TO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN---   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     BQ
)@@G@@LOCAL CODE CHANGES TO THIS ROUTINE SHOULD BE MADE WITH THE  @G@@@@. REALBR
)@@G@@IZATION THAT IT WILL SOON BE COMPLETELY REWRITTEN.  THIS REWRITE  @G@@@@BS
)@@G@@. WILL IMPLEMENT 2 MAJOR DESIGN CHANGES-- (1) THE PROPERTIES OF EACH    BT
)@@G@@@G@@@@. APL OPERATOR WILL BE DETERMINED FROM A TABLE, RATHER THAN BY TESBU
)@@G@@TING  @G@@@@. THE BINARY VALUE OF THE OPERATOR, AND (2) THE POLISH STRINBV
)@@G@@GS WILL     @G@@@@. BECOME A SEMI-PERMANENT PART OF THE WORKSPACE-- I.E.BW
)@@G@@ THE STORED CODE  @G@@@@. FOR A GIVEN APL STATEMENT WILL BE EITHER IN LEBX
)@@G@@XICAL FORM (AS NOW),    @G@@@@. OR IN POLISH FORM, BUT ONLY ONE OF THESEBY
)@@G@@ REPRESENTATIONS WILL EXIST   @G@@@@. IN THE WORKSPACE AT ANY ONE TIME. BZ
)@@G@@THIS CHANGE WILL MAKE IT UNNECESSARY@G@@@@. TO RE-COMPILE STATEMENTS WHICA
)@@G@@CH ARE EXECUTED, FOR EXAMPLE, IN A LOOP.  @G@@@@.  WE ARE PRESENTLY DESICB
)@@G@@GNING A MECHANISM TO ACCOUNT FOR THE FACT THAT  @G@@@@. THE CREATION OF CC
)@@G@@LOCAL VARIABLES MAY CAUSE THE PARSE OF SUCH STATEMENTS@G@@@@. TO CHANGE.CD
)@@G@@  IN THE NEW IMPLEMENTATION, THE POLISH STRINGS WILL BE     @G@@@@. PACKCE
)@@G@@ED 2 TOKENS PER WORD, RATHER THAN ONE AND A LEXICAL POINTER AS    @#@@@@CF
)@@G@@. IT IS DONE NOW. @G@@@@.     THIS CHANGE WILL OBVIOUSLY INCREASE SPEED CG
)@@G@@AND REDUCE WORKSPACE    @G@@@@. REQUIREMENTS.  IN ADDITION, IT WILL BE TCH
)@@G@@HE FIRST STEP IN AN EFFORT TO @F@@@@. PRODUCE AN APL SYSTEM WHICH WILL GCI
)@@G@@ENERATE ACTUAL 1100 SERIES    @G@@@@. COMPILED MACHINE INSTRUCTIONS, SUICJ
)@@G@@TABLE FOR INPUT TO THE COLLECTOR.   @[@@@@.     @F@@[[. THE PROCS BELOW CK
)@@G@@IMPLEMENT PHASE 1 OF THE ABOVE, I.E. TABULATION @[@@[[.     @#@@[[P     CL
)@@G@@  PROC   .  @A@@[[TMONAD* NAME   MONFUN         .     @A@@[[TDYAD*  NAMECM

)@@G@@       J     TI0040      . IF NOT, SYNTAX ERROR @E@@@@TI0010 LXPEEK TI00FB

)@@G@@F DECPT NOT FOL BY OP OR NOT OUTER, ERROR @G@[@@TI0050 ERROR YSYSTM,CO09FR

)@@G@@       . SYSERR   @[[@@@OUT . @#@@@@       LI$T  .    @]@@@@       END .FT

)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. SUBROUTINE INVOKED BY REFERENCES TO ABOVE PROC ---  IC

)@@G@@. THIS CALL IS TO REPLACE ( WITH [-- WE HAVE SCANNED (...)[ @C@@@@RP0050IW

)@@G@@ CALL REQUIRES US TO POP THE PAREN/BRACKET STACK@G@@@@RP0060 SSL   A1,36JB

)@@G@@OP INSTRUCTION    @E@@@@       LXI   A3,A5       . AND PUT POSN OF LEFT JH
)@@G@@MARK IN IT  @E@@@@       JE,U  A4,2 RP0080 . IF CLOSING A BRACE, GO STASJI
)@@G@@H NOP @D@@@@       TNE,U A4,3        . IS THIS A LIST CREATE OPN? @G@@@@JJ
)@@G@@       LXM,U A3,PSUDOF(PSOXQP,PSQMON)+ALLIST . YES, GENERATE THE OPCODE JK
)@@G@@@H@@@@       JNE,U A4,1 RP0070 . IF NOT BRACKET, DON'T GENERATE INDESINGJL
)@@G@@ OPCODE     @G@@@@       TE,U  A0,PSUDOF(PSOXQP,PSQXDY)+ASTORE . IS INDEJM
)@@G@@XING ALREADY SET? @G@@@@       LXM,U A3,PSUDOF(PSOXQP,PSQNIL)+PSNXNO . NJN
)@@G@@O, CHANGE NOP TO INDEX  @E@@@@RP0070 LXI,U A0,0,A2     . POST LEX INDEX JO
)@@G@@OF CLOSING DYAD   @F@@@@       SA    A0,1,A1     . SAVE DYADIC OP WHICH JP
)@@G@@CAUSED CLOSURE    @E@@@@RP0080 SA    A3,0,A1     . SAVE INDEX OR NOP, ASJQ
)@@G@@ APPROPRIATE@B@@@@       J     1,X11       . NORMAL EXIT    @A@@@@/. COMJR
)@@G@@PILE AN APL EXECUTABLE STMNT  @E@@@@. ENTER WITH ADDRESS OF LEXICAL TEXTJS
)@@G@@ FOR THIS STMNT IN A2   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@       INSTRS.    @ @@@@COMPILJT
)@@G@@* SX   X11,COLINK  .    @G@@@@       LMJ   X11,LEXGET  . INITIALIZE SCANJU
)@@G@@ OF LEXICALLY STORED TEXT     @ @@@@       J     CO0999      .    @E@@@@JV
)@@G@@       LMJ   X11,CODSTO  . INITIALIZE CODE STORAGE RTNE     @ @@@@      JW
)@@G@@ J     CO0999      .    @C@@@@       LA,U  A2,0        . CLEAR LEXICAL IJX
)@@G@@TEM NO@E@@@@       NILAD PSNXTS      . COMPILE 'GO TO NEXT STATEMENT'   JY
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@. ***** STATE 1, BEGIN STMNT *****  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@JZ
)@@G@@STATE1.     @D@@@@CP0100 SZ    CODTRM      . CLEAR DEFERRED TERM FLAG   KA
)@@G@@@C@@@@       SZ    COPREN      . NO PARENS ARE OPEN   @E@@@@       LXNEXKB
)@@G@@T CP0150,CP0110 CP0236,CP0190 . SCAN 1ST TERM   @G@@@@. GOT PRIMITIVE OPKC
)@@G@@R AFTER BEGIN-- ONLY END STMNT OR '(' ARE ALLOWED     @C@@@@CP0110 TE,U KD
)@@G@@ A0,AEOL     . IS THIS END OF STMNT?@C@@@@       TNE,U A0,ALAMP    . OR KE
)@@G@@START OF COMMENTS?@D@@@@       J     CO0300      . YES, GO CLOSE THE STAKF
)@@G@@TEMENT@G@@@@       JNE,U A0,AGOTO CP0230 . IF NOT RIGHT ARROW, GO CHECK KG
)@@G@@FOR MONAD   @E@@@@       LXPEEK CP0236     . IF NOT FOL BY OPR, TREAT ASKH
)@@G@@ MONAD@E@@@@CP0120 TE,U  A0,AEOL     . DOES END OF LINE FOLLOW ARROW?   KI
)@@G@@@D@@@@       TNE,U A0,ALAMP    . NO, HOW ABOUT COMMENTS?    @F@@@@      KJ
)@@G@@ J     CP0140      . IF EITHER, COMPILE STATEVECTOR CLEAR   @E@@@@      KK
)@@G@@ BACKUP            . ELSE RESTORE ORIGINAL PICKUP     @C@@@@       J    KL
)@@G@@ CP0236      . AND GO PROCESS MANAD @F@@@@CP0140 NILAD PSNESC      . SOLKM
)@@G@@ITARY RIGHT ARROW-- CLEAR STATEVECT @B@@@@       J     CO0300      . ANDKN
)@@G@@ GET OUT    @C@@@@. 1ST TERM IS OPERAND, CHECK FOR POSSIBLE LABEL @G@@@@KO
)@@G@@CP0150 LXPEEK,ACOLON CP0220   . IF NOT FOLLOWED BY COLON, NORMAL OP     KP
)@@G@@@E@@@@       J     CP0100      . OTHERWISE A LABEL, IGNORE IT     @[@@@@KQ
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@CP0190 ERROR YSYNTA,CO0930    . STMNTS CANNOT START WITH DYAKR
)@@G@@DIC FUNCS-  @[@@@@/.    @C@@@@. ****** STATE 2 --- AFTER AN OPERATOR ***KS
)@@G@@**    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@STATE2 .    @C@@@@CP0200 LXNEXT CP0220,CP0230 CPKT
)@@G@@0236,CP0295 .     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. ***** STATE 2A- AFTER A SEMICOLON KU
)@@G@@***** @[@@@@.     @]@@@@STAT2A .    @C@@@@CP0210 LXNEXT CP0220,CP0213 CPKV
)@@G@@0236,CP0295 .     @G@@@@CP0213 JNE,U A0,ASEMIC CP0215 . IF NOT SEMICOLONKW
)@@G@@, GO CHECK RITE BRACKET @E@@@@       NILAD PSNELX      . GENERATE ELIDEDKX
)@@G@@ INDEX MARKSTACK  @C@@@@       J     STAT2A      . CONTINUE THE MARCH   KY
)@@G@@@F@@@@CP0215 JNE,U A0,ARBRAK CP0230 . IF NOT RITE BRACKET, NORMAL MONAD KZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@       NILAD PSNELX      . YES, GENERATE SEMICOLON MARKSTACK@E@@@@LA
)@@G@@       J     CP0520      . AND GO PROCESS AFTER THE BRACKET @[@@@@.     LB
)@@G@@@B@@@@. BOTH OF THE ABOVE STATES CONVERGE HERE--@[@@@@.     @^@@@@. PICKLC
)@@G@@UP OF OPERAND     @G@@@@CP0220 DEFER             . DON'T GENERATE UNTIL LD
)@@G@@WE KNOW WHAT FOLLOWS    @ @@@@       J     STATE3      .    @G@@@@. GOT LE
)@@G@@PRIMITIVE-- IN THIS CONTEXT IT MAY BE A REDUCER OR NORMAL MONAD   @E@@@@LF
)@@G@@CP0230 TREDUC            . IS THIS AN OP WHICH CAN REDUCE?  @E@@@@      LG
)@@G@@ J     CP0234      . NO, FOLLOW NORMAL PROCEDURES     @G@@@@       LXPEELH
)@@G@@K CP0234     . YES, LOOK AHEAD FOR REDUCE FLAGS (1ST/LAST)  @G@@@@CP0231LI
)@@G@@ JNE,U A0,ARDFIR CP0232 . IF NOT RED ON 1ST, GO TRY NORMAL REDUCE @F@@@@LJ
)@@G@@       RESET             . RED ON 1ST COORD, GET ORIGINAL PARAMS  @G@@@@LK
)@@G@@       AA,U  A0,PSUDOF(0,PSQRED-PSQMON,PSFSLF)    . ADD REDUCE FLAG BITSLL
)@@G@@@D@@@@       J     CP0236      . AND GO GENERATE MONADIC OP @G@@@@CP0232LM
)@@G@@ JNE,U A0,AREDUC CP0233 . IF NOT NORMAL RED EITHER, BAKUP LOOKAHEA@F@@@@LN
)@@G@@       RESET             . NORMAL REDUCTION, GET ORIGINAL PARAMS  @G@@@@LO
)@@G@@       AA,U  A0,PSUDOF(0,PSQRED-PSQMON,0)    . ADD REDUCTION FLAGS TO OPLP
)@@G@@@F@@@@       J     CP0235      . AND GO LOOK FOR COORDINATE SELECTION   LQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@CP0233 BACKUP            . RESET LEX SCANNER AND ORIGINAL PARAMS  LR
)@@G@@@B@@@@. END OF TESTS FOR POSSIBLE REDUCTION--   @C@@@@CP0234 TMONAD     LS
)@@G@@       . IS THIS OP A MONAD?  @D@@@@       J     CP0240      . NO, GO CHLT
)@@G@@ECK FOR PAREN     @G@[@@       TSELEC            . YES, IS IT ALLOWED TOLU
)@@G@@ SELECT ON A COORD?     @G@@[[        TSELEM                . YES, IS ITLV
)@@G@@ ALLOWED TO SELECT A COORD?   @F[@@@       J     CP0236      . NO, GENERLW
)@@G@@ATE NORMAL MONADIC EXECUTE    @G@@@@CP0235 PEEKSL            . PEEK TO SLX
)@@G@@EE IF OP DOES IN FACT SELECT A COORD@F@@@@       J     CP0236      . IF LY
)@@G@@DOESN'T, GO GENERATE NORMAL MONAD   @E@@@@       MONAD             . IT LZ
)@@G@@DOES, GENERATE MONADIC EXECUTE@G@@@@       LBRACE            . AND CHAINMA
)@@G@@ THE OPENING LEFT BRACE OF SELECTION@E@@@@       J     STATE2      . THEMB
)@@G@@N CONTINUE AFTER THIS OPR     @E@@@@CP0236 MONAD             . GENERATE MC
)@@G@@NORMAL MONADIC EXECUTE  @D@@@@       J     STATE2      . CONTINUE AFTER MD
)@@G@@OPERATOR    @G@@@@CP0240 JNE,U A0,ALPAR CP0250  . IF NOT LEFT PAREN, TRYME
)@@G@@ LEFT LIST MARKER @#@@@@       LPAREN .   @ @@@@       J     STATE2     MF
)@@G@@ .    @G@@@@CP0250 JNE,U A0,ALLIST CO0910 . IF NOT LEFT LIST MARKER, SYNMG
)@@G@@TAX ERR     @D@@@@       LBLIST            . ADD MARKER TO PAREN CHAIN  MH
)@@G@@@ @@@@       J     STATE2      .    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@CP0295 ERROR YSYNTMI
)@@G@@A,CO0930    . DYADS MAY NOT FOLLOW OPERATORS    @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     MJ
)@@G@@@A@@@@. STATE 3 --- AFTER AN OPERAND *****@[@@@@.     @]@@@@STATE3 .    MK
)@@G@@@C@@@@CP0300 LXNEXT CP0310,CP0320 CO0910,CP0327 .     @#@@@@. PICKED UP ML
)@@G@@A TERM@B@@@@CP0310 J     CO0910      . SYNTAX ERROR   @A@@@@. PICKED UP MM
)@@G@@A PRIMITIVE OPERATOR ---@G@@@@CP0320 JNE,U A0,ASTORE CP0323 . IF OP IS NMN
)@@G@@OT STORE, GO CHECK FOR DYAD   @F@@@@       LA    A0,CODTRM   . IF STORE,MO
)@@G@@ GET THE DEFERRED OPERAND     @E@@@@       AA,U  A0,PSUDOF(PSOLOD) . MAKMP
)@@G@@E AN OPERATION OUT OF IT@D@@@@       DSL   A0,15       . ISOLATE THE PRIMQ
)@@G@@MARY OPCODE @G@@@@       JE,U  A0,PSOFUN CO0910      . STORING INTO A FUMR
)@@G@@NCT IS SYNTAX ERR @G@@@@       JNE,U A0,PSOLDV CP0322 . IF NOT LOAD AND MS
)@@G@@VERIFY, GO GENERATE CODE@F@@@@       SSL   A1,36-15    . IF LOAD WITH CHMT
)@@G@@ECK, GET RID OF CHECK   @E@@@@       SA    A1,CODTRM   . AND SAVE AS IF MU
)@@G@@A NORMAL OPERAND  @E@@@@CP0322 LA,U  A0,ASTORE   . REGENERATE THE ORIGINMV
)@@G@@AL STORE OP @C@@@@       J     CP0327      . AND GO GENERATE CODE @B@@@@MW
)@@G@@CP0323 TDYAD             . IS THIS A DYAD?@G@@@@       J     CP0330     MX
)@@G@@ . NO, GO LOOK FOR PARENS, SE7ICOLONS, ETC.     @G@@@@       TSTSEL     MY
)@@G@@       . DOES THIS OPR SELECT ALONG A COORDINATE+     @D@@@@       J    MZ
)@@G@@ CP0325      . NO, GENERATE NORMAL EXECUTE@E@@@@       DYAD             NA
)@@G@@ . YES, GENERATE REDUCING OPCODE    @C@@@@       LBRACE            . CHANB
)@@G@@IN THE LEFT BRACE @D@@@@       J     STATE2      . CONTINUE AFTER AN OPENC
)@@G@@RATOR @F@@@@CP0325 MODINR            . IF PART OF INNER PRODUCT, MODIFY ND
)@@G@@OPCODE@E@@@@CP0327 DYAD              . THEN GENERATE DYADIC EXECUTE     NE
)@@G@@@D@@@@       J     STATE2      . CONTINUE AFTER AN OPERATOR @E@@@@CP0330NF
)@@G@@ JE,U  A0,ACOLON CP0390      . IF COLON, LABEL ERROR  @D@@@@CP0340 JE,U NG
)@@G@@ A0,ALBRAK CP0345 . IS THIS LEFT BRACKET+ @C@@@@       SA    A0,COPGOT  NH
)@@G@@ . SAVE THE OPERATOR    @E@@@@       OPLOAD            . NO, GENERATE LONI
)@@G@@AD OF THIS OPERAND@D@@@@       J     CO0200      . CHECK FOR PARENS, ETCNJ
)@@G@@ .    @C@@@@CP0345 LBRACK            . CHAIN LEFT BRACKET   @F@@@@      NK
)@@G@@ OPLOAD            . LOAD DESCRIPTOR OF INDEXED VARIABLE    @E@@@@      NL
)@@G@@ J     STAT2A      . CONTINUE AS IF AFTER A SEMICOLON @ @@@@CP0390 ERRORNM
)@@G@@ YLABEL,CO0930 .  @[@@@@/.    @D@@@@. PROCESS RIGHT SIDE OF EXPR DELIMITNN
)@@G@@ER (E.G. ] OR ;  )@[@@@@.     @]@@@@CO0200 .    @D@@@@CP0500 LA    A0,CONO
)@@G@@PGOT   . PICK UP THE CHAR WE SCANNED@F@@@@       JE,U  A0,ASEMIC STAT2A NP
)@@G@@. IF SEMICOLON, GO SCAN AFTER IT    @G@@@@       JE,U  A0,ARBRAK CP0510 NQ
)@@G@@. IF RIGHT BRACKET, GO TEST FOR BRACE     @C@@@@       TE,U  A0,ARPAR   NR
)@@G@@ . IS IT RIGHT PAREN?   @E@@@@       TNE,U A0,ARLIST   . NO, HOW ABOUT RNS
)@@G@@IGHT SIDE OF LIST?@C@@@@       J     CP0530      . IF EITHER, GO PROCESSNT
)@@G@@@F@@@@       TE,U  A0,AEOL     . IF NONE OF ABOVE, MUST BE END OF LINE  NU

)@@G@@@@@@@@@[=[^&@@KAV\NBKSP$      K@#@#,L2([E @@@@@@@^6[AE@@TAV_SNOBOL      RY
)@@G@@@@D@@@M4XBJA]R(AWS^[H[F@@@]C4[@^2 GH@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@]C4# PUTVCRZ
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@#@@[@*  BUBBLESORT-I   @B[@@@   DEFINE('BUBBLESORT(A,M,N,F)SA
)@@G@@I,J,TEMP')  @[@@@@*     ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@SB
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@[@*  BUBBLESORT-F **************SC
)@@G@@******************************************@^]@@@*  BUBBLESORT(A,M,N,F)  SD
)@@G@@@G@@@@*  THIS DOES A BUBBLE SORT ON THE ARRAY A, FROM A[M] TO A[N], INCLSE
)@@G@@USIVE.@G@@@@*  THE FUNCTION F() DEFINES THE ORDERING; F(X,Y) SHOULD SUCCSF
)@@G@@EED IF X > Y@G@@@@*  AND FAIL IF X < Y.  IF X = Y, F(X,Y) CAN SUCCEED ORSG
)@@G@@ FAIL, BUT FAILURE@ @@@@*  WILL PRODUCE A FASTER SORT.@[@@@@*     @^@@@@SH
)@@G@@BUBBLESORT  I  =  M + 1 @E@@@@BUBBLEA   APPLY(F,A[I - 1],A[I])          SI
)@@G@@       :S(BUBBLEB)@G@@@@BUBBLEA1  I  =  LT(I,N)  I + 1                  SJ
)@@G@@ :S(BUBBLEA)F(RETURN)   @[@@@@*     @D@@@@*  A[I] IS OUT OF ORDER--BUBBLSK
)@@G@@E IT UP TO ITS PLACE:   @[@@@@*     @#@@[@BUBBLEB   J  =  I @^@@[@      SL
)@@G@@    TEMP  =  A[I] @ @@[@BUBBLEB1  A[J]  =  A[J - 1]   @F@@[@          J SM
)@@G@@ =  GT(J,M)  J - 1                   :F(BUBBLEB2)     @F@@[@          APSN
)@@G@@PLY(F,A[J - 1],TEMP)                 :S(BUBBLEB1)     @E@@[@BUBBLEB2  A[SO
)@@G@@J]  =  TEMP                          :(BUBBLEA1)@GA@@@******************SP
)@@G@@******************************************************___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@SQ
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@SR
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@#@@[@*  QUISS
)@@G@@CKSORT-I    @B[@@@   DEFINE('QUICKSORT(A,M,N,F)I,J,TEMP')   @[@@@@*     ST
)@@G@@___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@SU
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@[@*  QUICKSORT-F ***************************************SV
)@@G@@******************@^]@@@*  QUICKSORT(A,M,N,F)   @G@@@@*  THIS SORTS THE SW
)@@G@@ARRAY A, FROM A[M] TO A[N] (INCLUSIVE), ACCORDING TO  @G@@@@*  THE ORDERSX
)@@G@@ING DEFINED BY THE FUNCTION F.  F(X,Y) SHOULD SUCCEED IF    @G@@@@*  X >SY
)@@G@@ Y, AND FAIL IF X < Y.  IF X = Y, IT DOESN'T MATTER WHETHER F     @F@@@@SZ
)@@G@@*  SUCCEEDS OR FAILS, THOUGH FAILURE PRODUCES FASTER SORTING.     @[@@@@TA
)@@G@@*     @#@@[@QUICKSORT  I  =  M@#@@[@   TEMP  =  A[N]  @] @@@   J  =  N  TB
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @A@@@@*  TOP-DOWN SCAN FOR A[I] > TEMP:   @[@@@@*     @E@@@@TC
)@@G@@QUICKT   APPLY(F,A[I],TEMP)                      :S(QUICKTX)@G@@@@QUICKTTD
)@@G@@1  I  =  LT(I,J)  I + 1                    :S(QUICKT)F(QUICKS)    @E@@@@TE
)@@G@@QUICKTX  A[J]  =  A[I]                           :(QUICKB1) @[@@@@*     TF
)@@G@@@A@@@@* BOTTOM-UP SCAN FOR A[J] < TEMP:   @[@@@@*     @E@@@@QUICKB   APPTG
)@@G@@LY(F,TEMP,A[J])                      :S(QUICKBX)@G@@@@QUICKB1  J  =  LT(TH
)@@G@@I,J)  J - 1                    :S(QUICKB)F(QUICKS)    @E@@@@QUICKBX  A[ITI
)@@G@@]  =  A[J]                           :(QUICKT1) @[@@@@*     @B@@@@*  I =TJ
)@@G@@ J; RESTORE TEMP AND SORT SUBLISTS: @[@@@@*     @^@@@@QUICKS   A[I]  =  TK
)@@G@@TEMP  @C@@@@         GT(I - M,1)  QUICKSORT(A,M,I - 1,F)    @E@@@@      TL
)@@G@@   GT(N - J,1)  QUICKSORT(A,J + 1,N,F)     :(RETURN)  @G@@@@************TM
)@@G@@************************************************************___@@@@@@@@@TN
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@TO
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@TP
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@* GCD-D **********************************************TQ
)@@G@@******************@G@@@@* GCD(A,B) CALCULATES THE GREATEST COMMON DIVISOTR
)@@G@@R OF A AND B, USING     @G@@@@* EUCLID'S ALGORITHM.  A AND B ARE FIRST CTS
)@@G@@ONVERTED TO INTEGERS, AND     @G@@@@* IF THIS FAILS, GCD() FAILS.  IF EITT
)@@G@@THER IS ZERO, THE ABSOLUTE VALUE    @G@@@@* OF THE THE OTHER IS RETURNEDTU
)@@G@@.  IF BOTH ARE NON-ZERO, THE RESULT WILL  @^@@@@* BE A POSITIVE INTEGER.TV
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @G@@@@* THIS WAS WRITTEN BY JOHN M. CHAMBERS, C/O THE UWCC ITW
)@@G@@N MADISON (TEL.   @#@@@@* (608) 262-0926).@[@@@@*     @G@@@@* GCD WILL WTX
)@@G@@ORK FOR BOTH VERSION 2.0 AND VERSION 3.4 OF SNOBOL4.  IT    @G@@@@* COULTY
)@@G@@D BE IMPROVED FOR VERSION 3 BY USING REMDR(), BUT THIS HASN'T     @D@@@@TZ
)@@G@@* BEEN DONE BECAUSE IT WOULDN'T WORK WITH VERSION 2.  @[@@@@*     @G@@@@UA
)@@G@@* ALL LABELS AND FUNCTIONS START WITH 'GCD'.  THERE ARE NO GLOBAL NAMES.UB
)@@G@@@G@@@@******************************************************************UC
)@@G@@******___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@UD
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@]@@[@*  GCD-I    @^#@@@   DEFINE('GCD(A,B)')   @^@@@@   DEFUE
)@@G@@INE('GCD1(A,B)')  @[@@@@*     ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@UF
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@[@*  GCD-F *********************UG
)@@G@@******************************************@[J@@@*     @#@@@@*  GCD FUNCTUH
)@@G@@IONS: @E@@@@GCD  A  =  CONVERT(A,'INTEGER')                  :F(FRETURN)UI
)@@G@@@E@@@@     B  =  CONVERT(B,'INTEGER')                  :F(FRETURN)@E@@@@UJ
)@@G@@   GCD  =  EQ(A * B,0)  A + B                    :S(RETURN) @^@@@@     AUK
)@@G@@  =  LT(A,0)  -A  @^@@@@     B  =  LT(B,0)  -B  @E@@@@   GCD  =  LE(A,B)UL
)@@G@@  GCD1(A,B)                    :S(RETURN) @E@@@@   GCD  =  GCD1(B,A)    UM
)@@G@@                         :(RETURN)  @[@@@@*     @[@@@@GCD1  @E@@@@.  GCDUN
)@@G@@1  =  EQ( (B / A) * A , B)   A             :S(RETURN) @E@@@@   GCD1  =  UO
)@@G@@GCD1( B - (B / A) * A , A)           :(RETURN)  @G@@[@******************UP
)@@G@@******************************************************___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@UQ
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@UR
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@******************************************************US
)@@G@@******************@[@@@@*     @#@@@@*  INITIALIZATION:@[@@@@*     @B@@@@UT
)@@G@@   DELIMITER  =  IDENT(DELIMITER)   ':'   @ @@@@   WIDTH  =  IDENT(WIDTHUU
)@@G@@)  50 @ @@@@   UNITI  =  IDENT(UNITI)  5  @ @@@@   UNITO  =  IDENT(UNITOUV
)@@G@@)  1  @[@@@@*     @B@@@@   OUTPUT  =  '  DELIMITER: '  DELIMITER  @A@@@@UW
)@@G@@   OUTPUT  =  '      WIDTH: '  WIDTH@A@@@@   OUTPUT  =  ' INPUT UNIT: ' UX
)@@G@@ UNITI@A@@@@   OUTPUT  =  'OUTPUT UNIT: '  UNITO@[@@@@*     @ @@@@*  SETUY
)@@G@@ UP I/O OPERATIONS:     @[@@@@*     @A@@@@   OUTPUT('OUT',UNITO,'(80A1)'UZ
)@@G@@)     @^@@@@   INPUT('IN',UNITI,80) @[@@@@*     @^@@@@   DEFINE('AFTER(AVA
)@@G@@,B)') @B@@@@   DEFINE('PRODUCE(A,N)I,ID,LOC,LINE')    @C@@@@   DEFINE('RVB
)@@G@@EADLEVEL(L,A)C,B,I,ID,LOC,MAX,AA')  @^@@@@   DEFINE('SORT(A,M)')  @[@@@@VC
)@@G@@*     @B@@@@   DATA('ITEM(ID,LOC,DETAIL,N,LEVEL)')    @[@@@@*     @#@@@@VD
)@@G@@   &TRIM  =  1    @#@@@@   &ANCHOR  =  1  @ @@@@   BLANKS  =  SPAN(' ') VE
)@@G@@! ''  @^@@@@   B40  =  DUPL(' ',40) @[@@@@*     @#@@@@*  QUICKSORT-I    VF
)@@G@@@B@@@@   DEFINE('QUICKSORT(A,M,N,F)I,J,TEMP')   @[@@@@*     @G@@@@******VG
)@@G@@******************************************************************@[@@@@VH
)@@G@@*     @F@@@@*  GLOBAL CONTROL CODE.  READS IN INDEX, SORTS IT, AND PUNCHVI
)@@G@@ES IT.@[@@@@*     @[@@@@*     @^@@@@   INDEX  =  ARRAY(10)  @[@@@@*     VJ
)@@G@@@]@@@@   OUTPUT  =@A@@@@   OUTPUT  =  '****INPUT DECK:'     @]@@@@   OUTVK
)@@G@@PUT  =@E@@@@   NEXTCARD  =  IN                               :F(END)    VL
)@@G@@@#@@@@   GOTCARD  =  1  @^@@@@   OUTPUT  =  NEXTCARD  @^@@@@   NEXTCARD VM
)@@G@@ BLANKS . L @ @@@@   MAX  =  READLEVEL(L,.INDEX)@[@@@@*     @#@@@@   SORVN
)@@G@@T(INDEX,MAX)@[@@@@*     @]@@@@   OUTPUT  =@A@@@@   OUTPUT  =  '****OUTPUVO
)@@G@@T DECK:'    @]@@@@   OUTPUT  =@^@@@@   PRODUCE(INDEX,MAX)   @E@@@@      VP
)@@G@@                                           :(END)     @[@@@@*     @G@@@@VQ
)@@G@@************************************************************************VR
)@@G@@@G@@@@******************************************************************VS
)@@G@@******@^@@@@*  ORDERING FUNCTION:   @[@@@@*     @G@@@@AFTER  LGT(ID(A),IVT
)@@G@@D(B))                          :S(RETURN)F(FRETURN)   @G@@@@************VU
)@@G@@************************************************************@[@@@@*     VV
)@@G@@@#@@@@*  PRODUCE(A,N)   @[@@@@*     @G@@@@*  PRINT AND/OR PUNCH THE ARRAVW
)@@G@@Y A OF INDEX ITEMS; THERE ARE N ITEMS.    @[@@@@*     @[@@@@*     @#@@@@VX
)@@G@@PRODUCE  I  =  1  @[@@@@*     @^@@@@*  PRINT I-TH ITEM IN A:@[@@@@*     VY
)@@G@@@]@@@@PRODUCE.ITEM@A@@@@.  ID  =  LEVEL(A<I>)  ID(A<I>)     @C@@@@   ID VZ
)@@G@@ =  EQ(REMDR(SIZE(ID),2),1)   ID  ' '     @^@@@@   LOC  =  LOC(A<I>)    WA
)@@G@@@F@@@@   LINE  =  IDENT(LOC)  ID                       :S(PRODUCE.IT)   WB
)@@G@@@C@@@@   LOC  =  EQ(REMDR(SIZE(LOC),2),1)   '.'  LOC  @F@@@@   LINE  =  WC
)@@G@@ID  DUPL('. ',(WIDTH - SIZE(ID) - SIZE(LOC)) / 2)  LOC@F@@@@.           WD
)@@G@@                                     :F(PRODUCE.ERR)  @[@@@@*     @]@@@@WE
)@@G@@PRODUCE.IT  @#@@@@.  OUT  =  LINE   @#@@@@   OUTPUT  =  LINE@[@@@@*     WF
)@@G@@@^@@@@*  CHECK FOR SUB-ITEMS  @[@@@@*     @F@@@@   GT(N(A<I>),0)        WG
)@@G@@                         :F(PRODUCE.NEXT) @A@@@@   PRODUCE(DETAIL(A<I>),WH
)@@G@@ N(A<I>))   @]@@@@PRODUCE.NEXT@G@@@@.  I  =  LT(I,N)   I + 1            WI
)@@G@@        :S(PRODUCE.ITEM)F(RETURN)   @[@@@@*     @]@@@@PRODUCE.ERR @C@@@@WJ
)@@G@@.  OUTPUT  =  '*****FOLLOWING ITEM TOO BIG:'    @F@@@@   OUTPUT  =  ID  WK
)@@G@@DELIMITER  LOC                 :(PRODUCE.ITEM)  @G@@@@******************WL
)@@G@@******************************************************@G@@@@*  QUICKSORTWM
)@@G@@-F *********************************************************@^@@@@*  QUIWN
)@@G@@CKSORT(A,M,N,F)   @G@@@@*  THIS SORTS THE ARRAY A, FROM A[M] TO A[N] (INWO
)@@G@@CLUSIVE), ACCORDING TO  @G@@@@*  THE ORDERING DEFINED BY THE FUNCTION F.WP
)@@G@@  F(X,Y) SHOULD SUCCEED IF    @G@@@@*  X > Y, AND FAIL IF X < Y.  IF X =WQ
)@@G@@ Y, IT DOESN'T MATTER WHETHER F     @F@@@@*  SUCCEEDS OR FAILS, THOUGH FWR
)@@G@@AILURE PRODUCES FASTER SORTING.     @[@@@@*     @#@@@@QUICKSORT  I  =  MWS
)@@G@@@#@@@@   TEMP  =  A[N]  @]@@@@   J  =  N  @[@@@@*     @A@@@@*  TOP-DOWN WT
)@@G@@SCAN FOR A[I] > TEMP:   @[@@@@*     @E@@@@QUICKT   APPLY(F,A[I],TEMP)   WU
)@@G@@                   :S(QUICKTX)@G@@@@QUICKT1  I  =  LT(I,J)  I + 1       WV
)@@G@@             :S(QUICKT)F(QUICKS)    @E@@@@QUICKTX  A[J]  =  A[I]        WW
)@@G@@                   :(QUICKB1) @[@@@@*     @A@@@@* BOTTOM-UP SCAN FOR A[JWX
)@@G@@] < TEMP:   @[@@@@*     @E@@@@QUICKB   APPLY(F,TEMP,A[J])               WY
)@@G@@       :S(QUICKBX)@G@@@@QUICKB1  J  =  LT(I,J)  J - 1                   WZ
)@@G@@ :S(QUICKB)F(QUICKS)    @E@@@@QUICKBX  A[I]  =  A[J]                    XA
)@@G@@       :(QUICKT1) @[@@@@*     @B@@@@*  I = J; RESTORE TEMP AND SORT SUBLXB
)@@G@@ISTS: @[@@@@*     @^@@@@QUICKS   A[I]  =  TEMP  @C@@@@         GT(I - M,XC
)@@G@@1)  QUICKSORT(A,M,I - 1,F)    @E@@@@         GT(N - J,1)  QUICKSORT(A,J XD
)@@G@@+ 1,N,F)     :(RETURN)  @G@@@@******************************************XE
)@@G@@******************************@#@@@@*  READLEVEL(L,A) @[@@@@*     @G@@@@XF
)@@G@@*  READS CARDS STARTING WITH L (A STRING OF BLANKS) INTO THE ARRAY $A.  XG
)@@G@@@F@@@@*  IF THE ARRAY ISN'T BIG ENOUGH, IT WILL BE EXPANDED.  ANY INPUT XH
)@@G@@@F@@@@*  THAT STARTS WITH A LONGER STRING OF BLANKS IS READ IN AS A SUB-XI
)@@G@@@G@@@@*  LEVEL OF THE PREVIOUS ITEM; A SHORTER INITIAL BLANK STRING CAUSXJ
)@@G@@ES    @]@@@@*  A RETURN.@[@@@@*     @#@@@@READLEVEL  I  =  0@]@@@@   AA XK
)@@G@@ =  $A@^@@@@   MAX  =  PROTOTYPE(AA)@[@@@@*     @#@@@@*  GET A CARD:    XL
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @[@@@@READ.R@E@@@@.  GT(GOTCARD,0)                          XM
)@@G@@       :S(READ.R1)@E@@@@   GT(EOF,0)                                    XN
)@@G@@ :S(READ.S) @E@@@@   NEXTCARD  =  IN                               :F(REXO
)@@G@@AD.E) @^@@@@   OUTPUT  =  NEXTCARD  @]@@@@READ.R1     @#@@@@.  C  =  NEXXP
)@@G@@TCARD @#@@@@   GOTCARD  =  0  @[@@@@*     @F@@@@   C  BLANKS . B  (BREAKXQ
)@@G@@(DELIMITER) . ID  LEN(1)  REM . LOC  !    @ @@@@.     REM . ID  '' . LOCXR
)@@G@@)     @F@@@@   IDENT(B,L)                                    :F(READ.NEWXS
)@@G@@LEVEL)@#@@@@   I  =  I + 1    @E@@@@   GT(I,MAX)                        XT
)@@G@@             :F(READ.I) @[@@@@*     @^@@@@*  MUST EXPAND ARRAY    @[@@@@XU
)@@G@@*     @ @@@@   TEMP  =  ARRAY(MAX + 10)   @]@@@@   I  =  1  @ @@@@READ.LXV
)@@G@@  TEMP<I>  =  AA<I>     @E@@@@   I  =  LE(I,MAX)  I + 1                 XW
)@@G@@       :S(READ.L) @#@@@@   $A  =  TEMP    @#@@@@   AA  =  TEMP    @^@@@@XX
)@@G@@   MAX  =  MAX + 10     @[@@@@*     @^@@@@*  PROCESS THE ITEM:    @E@@@@XY
)@@G@@READ.I   AA<I>  =  ITEM(ID,LOC,,,L)              :(READ.R)  @[@@@@*     XZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @ @@@@*  CARD AT DIFFERENT LEVEL:   @[@@@@*     @#@@@@READ.NYA
)@@G@@EWLEVEL     @#@@@@.  GOTCARD  =  1  @E@@@@   L  B                       YB
)@@G@@                   :S(READ.S) @ @@@@   DETAIL(AA<I>)  =  ARRAY(10)@E@@@@YC
)@@G@@   N(AA<I>)  =  READLEVEL(B,.DETAIL(AA<I>))      :(READ.R)  @[@@@@*     YD
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @[@@@@*     @#@@@@READ.E  EOF  =  1 @E@@@@READ.S  READLEVEL YE
)@@G@@ =  I                          :(RETURN)  @G@@@@************************YF
)@@G@@************************************************@#@@@@*  SORT ROUTINE   YG
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @ @@@@SORT  QUICKSORT(A,1,M,'AFTER')@[@@@@*     @A@@@@*  FINYH
)@@G@@D SUB-LISTS AND SORT THEM     @[@@@@*     @[@@@@SORT1 @C@@@@.  GT(N(A<M>YI
)@@G@@),1)   SORT(DETAIL(A<M>),N(A<M>))   @G@@@@   M  =  GT(M,1)   M - 1      YJ
)@@G@@                   :S(SORT1)F(RETURN)     @[@@@@*     @G@@@@************YK
)@@G@@************************************************************@[@@@@END   YL
)@@G@@___]                           :(QUICKT1) @[@@@@*     @B@@@@*  I = J; REYM
)@@G@@STORE TEMP AND SORT SUBLISTS: @[@@@@*     @^@@@@QUICKS   A[I]  =  TEMP  YN
)@@G@@@C@@@@         GT(I - M,*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@* SORT-DATA-D ****************YO
)@@G@@******************************************@F@@@@* THE ELEMENT SNOBOL*LIBYP
)@@G@@.SORT-DATA IS A DECK PREPARED FOR TESTS OF@G@@@@* SORT ROUTINES.  IT CONYQ
)@@G@@SISTS OF ABOUT 150 CARDS, EACH OF WHICH HAS     @F@@@@* STARTING IN COLUYR
)@@G@@MN 1 THE NAME OF A TOWN IN THE UNITED STATES,   @F@@@@* CANADA, OR MEXICYS
)@@G@@O.  THERE ARE SEVERAL DUPLICATIONS IN THE LIST. @F@@@@* THE MOST OBVIOUSYT
)@@G@@ WAY TO SORT THEM IS ALPHABETICALLY, BUT THERE  @F@@@@* ARE LOTS OF OTHEYU
)@@G@@R POSSIBILITIES.  THERE IS A POSSIBILITY THAT   @G@@@@* THE NAMES OF THEYV
)@@G@@ STATES CONTAINING THE TOWNS WILL BE ADDED AT SOME    @#@@@@* FUTURE DATYW

)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@******************************AL
)@@G@@*****************************FREEZE-D*****@G@@@@* FREEZE(N,V,T) IS A TRAAM
)@@G@@CE FUNCTION THAT FREEZES THE VALUE OF $N TO     @G@@@@* THE VALUE V.  T AN
)@@G@@IS A TAG, AS IN NORMAL TRACING, WHICH WILL BE USED    @F@@@@* IN OUTPUT AO
)@@G@@IF N ISN'T A STRING (AND SO T SHOULD BE A STRING IF N @F@@@@* ISN'T).  IAP
)@@G@@F THE PROGRAM ASSIGNS A DIFFERENT VALUE TO $N AFTER IT@F@@@@* IS FROZEN,AQ
)@@G@@ A MESSAGE WILL BE PRINTED AS A WARNING AND $N WILL BE@ @@@@* RESET TO VAR
)@@G@@.  THUS IF WE DO: @ @@@@*        FREEZE('MAX',1000)   @A@@@@* AND LATER AS
)@@G@@TRY SOMETHING LIKE:     @^@@@@*        MAX  =  2000   @A@@@@* THE FOLLOWAT
)@@G@@ING WILL BE PRINTED:    @C@@@@*        *STMT <S>: MAX = 2000; FROZEN TO AU
)@@G@@1000  @F@@@@* WHERE <S> IS THE LINE NUMBER OF THE OFFENDING STATEMENT, AAV
)@@G@@ND MAX@F@@@@* WILL BE RETURNED TO ITS PERMANENT VALUE OF 1000.  A VARIABAW
)@@G@@LE CAN@A@@@@* BE UNFROZEN BY CALLING STOPTR(N). @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* TO IAX
)@@G@@NCORPORATE FREEZE() INTO A PROGRAM, THE FOLLOWING CARDS ARE USED: @A@@@@AY
)@@G@@*        @ADD  SNOBOL*LIB.FREEZE-I  @A@@@@*        @ADD  SNOBOL*LIB.FREEAZ
)@@G@@ZE-F  @G@@@@* THE FIRST IS INITIALIZATION, AND MUST BE EXECUTED BEFORE TBA
)@@G@@HE FIRST    @F@@@@* USE OF FREEZE().  THE SECOND IS FUNCTION CODE, AND SBB
)@@G@@HOULD NOT BE@E@@@@* EXECUTED, BUT JUST INCLUDED SOMEWHERE IN THE PROGRAMBC
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* NOTE THAT THIS FUNCTION, BEING A TRACE FUNCTIOBD
)@@G@@N, IS CONTROLLED BY     @G@@@@* &TRACE, AND WILL ONLY WORK IF &TRACE HASBE
)@@G@@ A POSITIVE VALUE.  THAT IS,  @E@@@@* ALL FREEZING WILL BE DISABLED IF &BF
)@@G@@TRACE IS TURNED OFF.    @[@@@@*     @F@@@@* ALL IDENTIFIERS (NAMES, FUNCBG
)@@G@@TIONS, LABELS) USED BY THE CODE FOR @G@@@@* FREEZE() START WITH THE STRIBH
)@@G@@NG 'FREEZE'.  SINCE INDIRECTION IS DONE ON@G@@@@* THE NAME N, FREEZE WONBI
)@@G@@'T WORK CORRECTLY IF APPLIED TO A NAME THAT IS  @G@@@@* THE SAME AS ONE BJ
)@@G@@OF ITS LOCAL NAMES.  THIS MEANS THAT NAMES STARTING   @G@@@@* WITH 'FREEBK
)@@G@@ZE' SHOULD NOT BE FROZEN--AT LEAST NOT WITHOUT CHECKING TO  @C@@@@* MAKEBL
)@@G@@ SURE THEY AREN'T NAMES USED BY FREEZE(). @[@@@@*     @D@@@@* FREEZE() WBM
)@@G@@AS TESTED WITH VERSION 3.4 OF SNOBOL4.    @G@@@@************************BN
)@@G@@***********************************FREEZE-D*****___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@BO
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@******BP
)@@G@@*****************************************************FREEZE-I*****@C@@@@BQ
)@@G@@   DEFINE('FREEZE(FREEZEN,FREEZEV,FREEZET)')    @E@@@@   DEFINE('FREEZERBR
)@@G@@(FREEZEN,FREEZET)FREEZES,FREEZEX,FREEZEY')@[@@@@*     @^@@@@   DATA('FREBS
)@@G@@EZET(V,T)') @G@@@@******************************************************BT
)@@G@@*****FREEZE-I*****___@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@******************************BU
)@@G@@*****************************FREEZE-F*****@^@@@@* SET UP A FROZEN NAME: BV
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @^@@@@FREEZE  STOPTR(FREEZEN) @^@@@@   $FREEZEN  =  FREEZEV BW
)@@G@@@G@@@@   TRACE(FREEZEN,'VALUE',FREEZET(FREEZEV,FREEZET),'FREEZER')   :(RBX
)@@G@@ETURN)@[@@@@*     @E@@@@* FUNCTION INVOKED IF A VALUE ASSIGNED TO A FROZBY
)@@G@@EN NAME:    @[@@@@*     @ @@@@FREEZER  FREEZES  =  &LASTNO  @^@@@@   FREBZ
)@@G@@EZEX  =  $FREEZEN @G@@@@   FREEZEX  =  IDENT(DATATYPE(FREEZEX),'STRING')CA
)@@G@@  ^'^  FREEZEX  ^'^     @E@@@@.                                         CB
)@@G@@       :S(FREEZE1)@E@@@@   FREEZEX  =  CONVERT(FREEZEX,'STRING')        CC
)@@G@@ :S(FREEZE1)@A@@@@   FREEZEX  =  DATATYPE(FREEZEX)    @F@@@@FREEZE1  IDECD
)@@G@@NT($FREEZEN,V(FREEZET))              :S(FREEZEOK)     @ @@@@   $FREEZEN CE
)@@G@@ =  V(FREEZET)    @^@@@@   FREEZEY  =  $FREEZEN @G@@@@   FREEZEY  =  IDECF
)@@G@@NT(DATATYPE(FREEZEY),'STRING')  ^'^  FREEZEY  ^'^     @E@@@@.           CG
)@@G@@                                     :S(FREEZE2)@E@@@@   FREEZEY  =  CONCH
)@@G@@VERT(FREEZEY,'STRING')         :S(FREEZE2)@A@@@@   FREEZEY  =  DATATYPE(CI
)@@G@@FREEZEY)    @G@@@@FREEZE2  FREEZEN  =  DIFFER(DATATYPE(FREEZEN),'STRING'CJ
)@@G@@)  T(FREEZET)     @F@@@@   OUTPUT  =  '* STMT '  FREEZES  ': '  FREEZEN CK
)@@G@@ ' = '  FREEZEX   @E@@@@.     '; FROZEN TO '  FREEZEY                   CL
)@@G@@ :(RETURN)  @[@@@@*     @G@@@@FREEZEOK  FREEZEN  =  DIFFER(DATATYPE(FREECM
)@@G@@ZEN),'STRING')  T(FREEZET)    @F@@@@   OUTPUT  =  '* STMT '  FREEZES  ':CN
)@@G@@ '  FREEZEN  ' = '  FREEZEX   @E@@@@.     '; AGREES WITH FROZEN VALUE.' CO
)@@G@@             :(RETURN)  @G@@@@******************************************CP
)@@G@@*****************FREEZE-F*****___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@CQ
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@******CR
)@@G@@*****************************************************MIN-MAX-D****@F@@@@CS
)@@G@@* MIN(X,Y) AND MAX(X,Y) RETURN THE MINIMUM AND MAXIMUM OF X AND Y,@F@@@@CT
)@@G@@* RESPECTIVELY.  THEY WILL FAIL IF EITHER ARGUMENT IS NON-NUMERIC.@G@@@@CU
)@@G@@* IF X AND Y ARE EQUAL, BUT OF DIFFERENT TYPES, X WILL BE RETURNED.     CV
)@@G@@@C@@@@* THUS, MIN(1,'1') = 1, WHILE MIN('1',1) = '1'. @[@@@@*     @G@@@@CW
)@@G@@* TO USE MIN() AND MAX(), INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING CARDS IN A PROGRAM:     CX
)@@G@@@A@@@@*     @ADD  SNOBOL*LIB.MIN-MAX-I    @A@@@@*     @ADD  SNOBOL*LIB.MCY
)@@G@@IN-MAX-F    @G@@@@* THE FIRST CONTAINS CALLS OF DEFINE(); THE SECOND CONCZ
)@@G@@TAINS FUNCTION    @]@@@@* CODE.     @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* MIN() AND MAX() DA
)@@G@@WERE TESTED WITH VERSION 3.4 OF SNOBOL4, BUT SHOULD   @^@@@@* WORK WITH DB
)@@G@@ANY VERSION.@[@@@@*     @G@@@@* THE ONLY FUNCTIONS DEFINED ARE MIN() ANDDC
)@@G@@ MAX(), AND THE ONLY LABELS   @D@@@@* ARE 'MIN' AND 'MAX'.  THERE ARE NODD
)@@G@@ GLOBAL NAMES.    @[@@@@*     @ @@@@* CODED BY JOHN M. CHAMBERS.  @G@@@@DE
)@@G@@***********************************************************MIN-MAX-D****DF
)@@G@@___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@DG
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@DH
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@******************************************************DI
)@@G@@*****MIN-MAX-I****@^@@@@   DEFINE('MIN(MIN,X)') @^@@@@   DEFINE('MAX(MAXDJ
)@@G@@,X)') @G@@@@***********************************************************MDK
)@@G@@IN-MAX-I****___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@DL
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@******DM
)@@G@@*****************************************************MIN-MAX-F****@E@@@@DN
)@@G@@MAX  MAX  =  LT(MAX,X)  X                        :S(RETURN) @G@@@@     GDO
)@@G@@E(MAX,X)                                   :S(RETURN)F(FRETURN)   @[@@@@DP
)@@G@@*     @E@@@@MIN  MIN  =  GT(MIN,X)  X                        :S(RETURN) DQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@     GE(MIN,X)                                   :S(RETURN)F(FRETUDR
)@@G@@RN)   @G@@@@***********************************************************MDS
)@@G@@IN-MAX-F****___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@* BUBBDT
)@@G@@LESORT-D *********************************************************@G@@@@DU
)@@G@@* BUBBLESORT(A,M,N,F) SORTS THE ONE-DIMENSIONAL ARRAY A FROM A<M> TO    DV
)@@G@@@G@@@@* A<N> INCLUSIVE, ACCORDING TO THE ORDERING DEFINED BY THE FUNCTIODW
)@@G@@N F.  @B@[@@* IF M - N < 2, ITS BEHAVIOR IS UNDEFINED.@B@@[[* IF M - N <DX
)@@G@@ 1, ITS BEHAVIOR IS UNDEFINED.@[[@@@*     @F@@@@* THE FUNCTION F SHOULD DY
)@@G@@WORK AS FOLLOWS:  F(X,Y) SHOULD SUCCEED IF@G@@@@* X > Y (THAT IS, X SHOUDZ
)@@G@@LD FOLLOW Y) IN THE ORDERING DESIRED; F(X,Y)    @G@@@@* SHOULD FAIL IF XEA
)@@G@@ < Y.  IF X = Y, IT DOESN'T MATTER WHETHER F(X,Y)     @F@@@@* SUCCEEDS OEB
)@@G@@R FAILS, BUT FAILURE IS PREFERABLE FOR TWO REASONS: IT@G@@@@* PRODUCES AEC
)@@G@@ FASTER SORT, AND IT WILL LEAVE EQUAL ITEMS IN THE SAME     @B@@@@* RELAED
)@@G@@TIVE ORDER AS THEY WERE ORIGINALLY. @[@@@@*     @F@@@@* FOR EXAMPLE, TO EE
)@@G@@PUT A<1> THROUGH A<P> IN ALPHABETIC ORDER, CALL:@ @@@@*     BUBBLESORT(AEF
)@@G@@,1,P,'LGT') @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* BUBBLESORT IS A USEFUL SORT IF THE THINGEG
)@@G@@S TO BE SORTED ARE ALMOST     @G@@@@* IN THE CORRECT ORDER TO START WITHEH
)@@G@@.  FOR RANDOM DATA, IT IS A RATHER  @F@@@@* SLOW SORT, AND OTHER METHODSEI
)@@G@@ (SUCH AS QUICKSORT) ARE PREFERABLE.@[@@@@*     @G@@@@* THE SORT IS DONEEJ
)@@G@@ BY A LINEAR SCAN FROM A<M+1> TO A<N>, LOOKING FOR    @G@@@@* ITEMS THATEK
)@@G@@ SHOULD PRECEDE THEIR PREDECESSORS.  WHEN SUCH AN ITEM IS   @G@@@@* FOUNEL
)@@G@@D, IT IS MOVED UP (TOWARDS A<M>) UNTIL IT IS IN ITS CORRECT PLACE,@G@@@@EM
)@@G@@* AND ALL INTERVENING ITEMS ARE MOVED DOWN ONE PLACE.  IT IS EASY TO    EN
)@@G@@@G@@@@* SEE WHY IT WILL WORK VERY QUICKLY FOR ALMOST-SORTED DATA AND SLOEO
)@@G@@W DOWN@D@@@@* RATHER BADLY WHEN THE DATA GETS BADLY OUT OF ORDER. @[@@@@EP
)@@G@@*     @G@@@@* ALL LABELS IN THE CODE START WITH 'BUBBLE'.  THE ONLY FUNCEQ
)@@G@@TION DEFINED@G@@@@* IS 'BUBBLESORT', AND THERE ARE NO GLOBAL NAMES USED.ER
)@@G@@  THE CODE CAN    @D@@@@* BE INCORPORATED INTO A SNOBOL4 PROGRAM BY USINES
)@@G@@G:    @A@@@@*     @ADD  SNOBOL*LIB.BUBBLESORT-I @A@@@@*     @ADD  SNOBOLET
)@@G@@*LIB.BUBBLESORT-F @F@@@@* THE FIRST IS INITIALIZATION AND MUST BE EXECUTEU
)@@G@@ED BEFORE CALLING @C@@@@* BUBBLESORT(); THE SECOND IS THE FUNCTION CODE.EV
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @A@@@@* THIS FUNCTION WAS WRITTEN BY:     @^@@@@*     JOHN MEW
)@@G@@. CHAMBERS  @A@@@@*     UNIV. OF WIS. COMPUTING CENTER@^@@@@*     1210 WEX
)@@G@@. DAYTON ST.@ @@@@*     MADISON, WIS.  53706    @ @@@@*     TEL. (608) 2EY
)@@G@@62-0926     @[@@@@*     @E@@@@* BUBBLESORT HAS BEEN TESTED FOR VERSION 3EZ
)@@G@@.4 OF SNOBOL4     @G@@@@************************************************FA
)@@G@@************************___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@FB
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@* QUICFC
)@@G@@KSORT-D **********************************************************@G@@@@FD
)@@G@@* QUICKSORT(A,M,N,F) SORTS THE ONE-DIMENSIONAL ARRAY A FROM A<M> TO     FE
)@@G@@@G@@@@* A<N> INCLUSIVE, ACCORDING TO THE ORDERING DEFINED BY THE FUNCTIOFF
)@@G@@N F.  @F@]@@* M - N SHOULD BE > 1, AND NO CHECKING IS DONE TO ENSURE THIFG
)@@G@@S.    @F@@[]* M - N SHOULD BE > 0, BUT NO CHECKING IS DONE TO ENSURE THIFH
)@@G@@S.    @[[@@@*     @G@@@@* THE FUNCTION F SHOULD BEHAVE AS FOLLOWS:  F(X,FI
)@@G@@Y) SHOULD SUCCEED IF    @G@@@@* X > Y (THAT IS, X SHOULD FOLLOW Y) IN THFJ
)@@G@@E DESIRED ORDERING, AND FAIL  @G@@@@* IF X < Y.  IF X = Y, IT DOESN'T MAFK
)@@G@@TTER WHETHER F(X,Y) SUCCEEDS OR     @G@@@@* FAILS, BUT FAILURE WILL PRODFL
)@@G@@UCE A FASTER SORT.  THE RELATIVE ORDER    @G@@@@* OF EQUAL ITEMS (DEFINEFM
)@@G@@D AS ITEMS X AND Y FOR WHICH F(X,Y) AND F(Y,X)  @G@@@@* BOTH FAIL OR BOTFN
)@@G@@H SUCCEED) IS FOR ALL PRACTICAL PURPOSES UNPREDICT-   @]@@@@* ABLE.     FO
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @F@@@@* THE ALGORITHM USED IS DESCRIBED IN THE REFERENCES.  FP
)@@G@@[2] HAS AN  @G@@@@* ESPECIALLY LUCID DESCRIPTION; THIS ROUTINE IS ESSENTFQ
)@@G@@IALLY A LITERAL   @^@@@@* TRANSLATION OF IT.    @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* QUICFR
)@@G@@KSORT IS APPARENTLY THE FASTEST IN-MEMORY SORT KNOWN FOR RANDOMLY @G@]@@FS
)@@G@@* ORDERED DATA.  FOR N ITEMS, THE SORT TIME IS PROPORTIONAL TO 2 * N *  FT
)@@G@@@D@]@@* LN(N), WHERE LN(X) IS THE NATURAL LOGARITHM OF X.   @G@@[]* ORDEFU
)@@G@@RED DATA.  FOR N ITEMS, THE SORT TIME IS PROPORTIONAL TO N * LN(N)@C@@[]FV
)@@G@@* WHERE LN(X) IS THE NATURAL LOGARITHM OF X.    @[]@@@*     @F@@@[* TO UFW
)@@G@@SE QUICKSORT, INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING CARDS IN YOUR PROGRAM:  @A@@@[*     FX
)@@G@@@ADD  SNOBOL*LIB.QUICKSORT-I  @A@@@[*     @ADD  SNOBOL*LIB.QUICKSORT-F  FY
)@@G@@@F@@@[* THE FIRST IS INITIALIZATION AND MUST BE EXECUTED BEFORE CALLING FZ
)@@G@@@C@@@[* QUICKSORT(); THE SECOND IS THE FUNCTION CODE. @[@@@[*     @A@@@@GA
)@@G@@* THIS ROUTINE WAS IMPLEMENTED BY:  @^@@@@*     JOHN M. CHAMBERS  @A@@@@GB
)@@G@@*     UNIV. OF WIS. COMPUTING CENTER@^@@@@*     1210 W. DAYTON ST.@ @@@@GC
)@@G@@*     MADISON, WIS.  53706    @ @@@@*     TEL. (608) 262-0926     @[@@@@GD
)@@G@@*     @C@@@@* IT WAS DEBUGGED USING VERSION 3.4 OF SNOBOL4. @[@@@@*     GE
)@@G@@@G@@@@* ALL LABELS USED START WITH 'QUICK'.  THERE ARE NO GLOBAL NAMES, GF
)@@G@@AND   @C@@@@* THE ONLY FUNCTION DEFINED IS 'QUICKSORT'.     @[@@@@*     GG
)@@G@@@#@@@@* REFERENCES:     @G@@@@* 1. HOARE, C.A.R.; ALGORITHM 64, QUICKSORGH
)@@G@@T; CACM 4, 7 (JULY 1961), 321.@[@[@@* 2.  @G@@@[* 2. BRAWN, B.S.; GUSTAVGI
)@@G@@SON, F.G.; MANKIN, E.S.; SORTING IN A PAGING    @C@@@[*    ENVIRONMENT; GJ
)@@G@@CACM 13, 8 (AUG 1970), 483.   @G@@@@* 3. VAN EMDEN, M.H.; INCREASING THEGK
)@@G@@ EFFICIENCY OF QUICKSORT; CACM 13, 9@^@[@@* (SEPT 1970), 563.     @^@@@[GL
)@@G@@*    (SEPT 1970), 563.  @G@@@@******************************************GM

)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@*************************************************PATCHGO
)@@G@@MERGE-D***********@G@@@@* PATCHMERGE IS A PROGRAM THAT MERGES DECKS OF PGP
)@@G@@ATCH CARDS THAT ARE     @G@@@@* IN THE UNIVAC 1108 PATCH-DECK FORMAT.  TGQ
)@@G@@HAT IS, EACH BLOCK OF PATCHES @F@@@@* IS PRECEDED BY A 'PATCH CONTROL CAGR
)@@G@@RD' THAT STARTS WITH A SPECIAL@G@@@@* CHARACTER (USUALLY A '-'), AND THIGS
)@@G@@S CONTROL CARD SAYS WHERE TO PUT    @D@@@@* THE PATCHES.  A CONTROL CARDGT
)@@G@@ CAN HAVE TWO FORMATS:  @A@@@@*     1)  '-'  INTEGER . I  ' '     @D@@@@GU
)@@G@@*     2)  '-'  INTEGER . I  ','  INTEGER . J  ' '     @G@@@@* THE FIRST GV
)@@G@@MEANS TO INSERT THE CARDS THAT FOLLOW IT AFTER THE I-TH     @G@@@@* CARDGW
)@@G@@ OF THE SOURCE DECK.  THE SECOND MEANS TO REPLACE THE I-TH THRU   @G@@@@GX
)@@G@@* THE J-TH CARDS, INCLUSIVE.  ANY CARDS AT THE START OF A DECK THAT     GY
)@@G@@@F@@@@* AREN'T PRECEDED BY A CONTROL CARD ARE TO BE INSERTED BEFORE THE GZ
)@@G@@@A@@@@* FIRST CARD OF THE SOURCE DECK.    @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* THE INITIAHA
)@@G@@L STRING THAT IDENTIFIES CONTROL CARDS CAN BE CHANGED BY    @E@@@@* PRECHB
)@@G@@EDING A PATCH DECK WITH A CARD THAT HAS THE FORMAT:   @ @@@@*     '-='  HC
)@@G@@BREAK(' ') . CC   @D@@@@* AND THEN CC WILL BE USED INSTEAD OF THE USUAL HD
)@@G@@'-'.  @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* PATCHMERGE MERGES TWO SUCH PATCH DECKS IN THE HE
)@@G@@OBVIOUS WAY.  IT HAS    @C@@@@* TWO INPUT FILES AND AN OUTPUT FILE AS FOHF
)@@G@@LLOWS:@F@@@@*     INUNIT1 = UNIT NUMBER OF PRIMARY PATCH DECK, DEFAULTS HG
)@@G@@TO 5. @G@@@@*     INUNIT2 = UNIT NUMBER OF SECONDARY PATCH DECK, DEFAULTHH
)@@G@@S TO 10.    @F@@@@*     OUTUNIT = UNIT NUMBER OF OUTPUT FILE, DEFAULTS THI
)@@G@@O 1 (PUNCH).@D@@@@* A LISTING IS ALSO GENERATED ON THE PRINTER, UNIT 6. HJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @G@@@@* IF THERE ARE CONFLICTS BETWEEN THE TWO SETS OF PATCHHK
)@@G@@ES, THOSE FROM    @F@@@@* INUNIT1 WILL BE USED, AND THOSE FROM INUNIT2 WHL
)@@G@@ILL BE IGNORED.   @G@@@@* WHENEVER THIS HAPPENS, A MESSAGE WILL BE PRINTHM
)@@G@@ED IN THE LISTING AS    @]@@@@* A WARNING.@[@@@@*     @G@@@@* THERE IS AHN
)@@G@@ SPECIAL WAY OF INDICATING CHANGES TO INITIAL BLOCKS OF     @G@@@@* PATCHO
)@@G@@HES, SINCE IT IS IMPOSSIBLE TO OVERWRITE THEM BY USING A CONFLICT @G@@@@HP
)@@G@@* IN CONTROL CARDS.  IF BOTH DECKS HAVE INITIAL BLOCKS OF PATCHES, THOSEHQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@* FROM INUNIT1 WILL BE PUT BEFORE THOSE FROM INUNIT2.  IT IS POSSIHR
)@@G@@BLE TO@F@@@@* REVERSE THEIR ORDER OR OVERWRITE THOSE FROM INUNIT2 BY USIHS
)@@G@@NG TWO@A@@@@* SPECIAL CONTROL CARDS IN INUNIT1: @#@@@@*     1)  '-0'    HT
)@@G@@@#@@@@*     2)  '-0,0'  @G@@@@* THE FIRST CAUSES THE CARDS THAT FOLLOW IHU
)@@G@@T TO BE PUT AFTER THE INITIAL @G@@@@* CARDS FROM INUNIT2.  THE SECOND CAHV
)@@G@@USES THE INITIAL BLOCK OF INUNIT2   @F@@@@* (IF ONE EXISTS) TO BE DELETEHW
)@@G@@D AND REPLACED BY ANY INITIAL CARDS @G@@@@* FROM INUNIT1.  NEITHER OF THHX
)@@G@@ESE 'FAKE' CONTROL CARDS WILL APPEAR IN   @#@@@@* THE OUTPUT DECK.@[@@@@HY
)@@G@@*     @D@@@@* PATCHMERGE CAN BE EXECUTED BY SOMETHING OF THE FORM:@#@@@@HZ
)@@G@@*     @SNOBOL     @A@@@@*        --FILE UNITS DEFINED--     @A@@@@*     IA
)@@G@@@ADD  SNOBOL*LIB.PATCHMERGE   @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* FOR EXAMPLE, IF WE HAVIB
)@@G@@E A DECK OF PATCHES IN FILE 15 AND WANT TO ADD  @G@@@@* MORE PATCHES THAIC
)@@G@@T HAVE BEEN PUNCHED ON CARDS, AND THEN USE THE NEW    @F@@@@* PATCH DECKID
)@@G@@ TO UPDATE THE ELEMENT A.B, WE COULD DO THE FOLLOWING:@#@@@@*     @SNOBOIE
)@@G@@L     @^@@@@*        INUNIT2  =  15 @^@@@@*        OUTUNIT  =  16 @A@@@@IF
)@@G@@*     @ADD  SNOBOL*LIB.PATCHMERGE   @A@@@@*        --NEW PATCHES GO HEREIG
)@@G@@--    @#@@@@*     @ELT,UL  A.B@#@@@@*     @ADD  16.   @[@@@@*     @G@@@@IH
)@@G@@* PATCHMERGE WAS WRITTEN BY JOHN M. CHAMBERS, AND DEBUGGED USING VERSIONII
)@@G@@@B@@@@* 3.4 OF SNOBOL4 DURING JANUARY 1971.     @G@@@@******************IJ
)@@G@@*******************************PATCHMERGE-D***********___ROL CARD ARE TOIK
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@*************************************************PATCHIL
)@@G@@MERGE*************@[@@@@*     @A@@@@   INUNIT1  =  IDENT(INUNIT1)  5    IM
)@@G@@@A@@@@   INUNIT2  =  IDENT(INUNIT2)  10   @A@@@@   OUTUNIT  =  IDENT(OUTIN
)@@G@@UNIT)  1    @[@@@@*     @ @@@@   INPUT('IN1',INUNIT1,80)    @ @@@@   INPIO
)@@G@@UT('IN2',INUNIT2,80)    @A@@@@   OUTPUT('OUT',OUTUNIT,'(80A1)')   @[@@@@IP
)@@G@@*     @ @@@@   INT  =  SPAN('1234567890') @#@@@@   CC  =  '-'     @B@@@@IQ
)@@G@@   CCPAT  =  '-='  (BREAK(' ') ! REM) . CC@^@@@@   B80  =  DUPL(' ',80) IR
)@@G@@@#@@@@   &ANCHOR  =  1  @#@@@@   &TRIM  =  1    @[@@@@*     @[@@@@*     IS
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @C@@@@*  READ IN INITIAL CARDS, CHECK FOR '-=' CARDS. @[@@@@IT
)@@G@@*     @E@@@@I1 C1  =  IN1                                    :F(EOF1A)  IU
)@@G@@@E@@@@   C1  CCPAT                                     :F(I2)     @#@@@@IV
)@@G@@   OUT  =  C1     @#@@@@   OUTPUT  =  C1  @E@@@@   C1  =  IN1           IW
)@@G@@                         :F(EOF1A)  @E@@@@I2 C2  =  IN2                 IX
)@@G@@                   :F(EOF2)   @E@@@@   C2  CCPAT                        IY
)@@G@@             :F(INITCC) @#@@@@   OUT  =  C2     @#@@@@   OUTPUT  =  C2  IZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@   C2  =  IN2                                    :F(EOF2)   @[@@@@JA
)@@G@@*     @A@@@@*  DEFINE CONTROL-CARD PATTERNS     @[@@@@*     @[@@@@INITCCJB
)@@G@@@F@@@@   CC1PAT  =   CC  INT . MIN1  (','  INT . MAX1  !  '' . MAX1)    JC
)@@G@@@F@@@@   CC2PAT  =   CC  INT . MIN2  (','  INT . MAX2  !  '' . MAX2)    JD
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @F@@@@*  INITIAL PATCHES--SEE IF THEY EXIST AT ALL, AND TAKEJE
)@@G@@ CARE OF    @E@@@@*  THEM IF THEY DO.  NOTE CODE FOR '-0' AND '-0,0' CARJF
)@@G@@DS.   @[@@@@*     @]@@@@INITCC1     @E@@@@   C1 CC1PAT                  JG
)@@G@@                   :S(INITCC0)@[@@@@*     @C@@@@*  NO CONTROL CARD--COPYJH
)@@G@@ BLOCK FROM UNIT 1.     @[@@@@*     @#@@@@IB1   OUT  =  C1  @#@@@@   OUTJI
)@@G@@PUT  =  C1  @G@@@@   C1  =  IN1                                    :F(EOJJ
)@@G@@F1)S(INITCC1)     @[@@@@*     @D@@@@*  FIRST CONTROL CARD FROM 1--IS IT JK
)@@G@@'-0' OR '-0,0'?   @[@@@@*     @]@@@@INITCC0     @F@@@@   EQ(MIN1,0)  IDEJL
)@@G@@NT(MAX1)                       :F(INITCC00)     @[@@@@*     @C@@@@*  '-0JM
)@@G@@', INSERT AFTER INITIAL BLOCK FROM UNIT 2.@[@@@@*     @#@@@@IB2   OUT  =JN
)@@G@@  C2  @#@@@@   OUTPUT  =  C2  @E@@@@   C2  =  IN2                       JO
)@@G@@             :F(EOF2)   @E@@@@   C2  CC2PAT                             JP
)@@G@@       :F(IB2)    @[@@@@*     @A@@@@*  AND ADD THE BLOCK FROM UNIT 1.   JQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @[@@@@IB2-1 @E@@@@   C1  =  IN1                             JR
)@@G@@       :F(EOF1)   @E@@@@   C1  CC1PAT                                   JS
)@@G@@ :S(MAIN)   @#@@@@   OUT  =  C1     @E@@@@   OUTPUT  =  C1              JT
)@@G@@                   :(IB2-1)   @[@@@@*     @A@@@@*  '-0,0', REPLACE BLOCKJU
)@@G@@ FROM 2.    @[@@@@*     @]@@@@INITCC00    @E@@@@   EQ(MIN1,0)  EQ(MAX1,0JV
)@@G@@)                        :F(INITCC2)@E@@@@   C2  =  IN2                 JW
)@@G@@                   :F(EOF2)   @G@@@@   C2  CC2PAT                       JX
)@@G@@             :S(IB2-1)F(INITCC00)   @[@@@@*     @E@@@@*  UNIT 1 STARTS WJY
)@@G@@ITH CONTROL CARD--CHECK FOR INITIAL CARDS @B@@@@*  FROM UNIT 2, AND COPYJZ
)@@G@@ THEM IF PRESENT. @[@@@@*     @]@@@@INITCC2     @E@@@@   C2  CC2PAT     KA
)@@G@@                               :S(MAIN)   @#@@@@   OUT  =  C2     @#@@@@KB
)@@G@@   OUTPUT  =  C2  @G@@@@   C2  =  IN2                                   KC
)@@G@@ :F(EOF2)S(INITCC2)     @[@@@@*     @[@@@@*     @D@@@@*  MAIN BLOCK--C1 KD
)@@G@@AND C2 BOTH CONTAIN CONTROL CARDS.  @F@@@@*  COMPARE THEM, AND OUTPUT THKE
)@@G@@E APPROPRIATE BLOCK OF PATCHES.     @[@@@@*     @[@@@@*     @[@@@@MAIN  KF
)@@G@@@#@@@@   TYPE1  =  'A'  @ @@@@   TYPE1  =  IDENT(MAX1)  'F' @D@@@@   MAXKG
)@@G@@1  =  IDENT(MAX1)  MIN1                    :(C2)@[@@@@*     @A@@@@*  SETKH
)@@G@@ UP CONTROL INFO FOR FILE 1.  @[@@@@*     @#@@@@C1 TYPE1  =  'A'  @ @@@@KI
)@@G@@   TYPE1  =  IDENT(MAX1)  'F' @E@@@@   MAX1  =  IDENT(MAX1)  MIN1       KJ
)@@G@@             :(TEST)    @[@@@@*     @A@@@@*  SET UP CONTROL INFO FOR FILKK
)@@G@@E 2.  @[@@@@*     @#@@@@C2 TYPE2  =  'A'  @ @@@@   TYPE2  =  IDENT(MAX2)KL
)@@G@@  'F' @ @@@@   MAX2  =  IDENT(MAX2)  MIN2 @[@@@@*     @C@@@@*  CONTROL IKM
)@@G@@NFO SET UP--WHICH ONE GOES FIRST?   @[@@@@*     @E@@@@TEST  LE(MAX1,MIN2KN
)@@G@@)                              :S(X1-2)   @E@@@@      LE(MAX2,MIN1)     KO
)@@G@@                         :S(X2-1)   @[@@@@*     @E@@@@*  THEY OVERLAP, PKP
)@@G@@RINT MESSAGE AND DELETE BLOCK FROM UNIT 2.@[@@@@*     @B@@@@OLAP  OUTPUTKQ
)@@G@@  =  B80  '**DELETED: '  C2   @[@@@@*     @A@@@@*  SKIP OVER BLOCK FROM KR
)@@G@@UNIT 2:     @[@@@@*     @]@@@@FIND2CC     @E@@@@   C2  =  IN2           KS
)@@G@@                         :F(EOF2)   @F@@@@   C2  CC2PAT                 KT
)@@G@@                   :F(FIND2CC)S(C2) @[@@@@*     @B@@@@*  MAX1 <= MIN2, OKU
)@@G@@UTPUT BLOCK FROM UNIT1. @[@@@@*     @[@@@@X1-2  @E@@@@   IDENT(TYPE1,'F'KV
)@@G@@)  EQ(MAX1,MIN2)               :S(OLAP)   @F@@@@   IDENT(TYPE1,'A')  IDEKW
)@@G@@NT(TYPE2,'A')  EQ(MAX1,MIN2)  :S(OLAP)    @#@@@@X1-2A OUT  =  C1  @#@@@@KX
)@@G@@   OUTPUT  =  C1  @E@@@@   C1  =  IN1                                   KY
)@@G@@ :F(EOF1)   @F@@@@   C1  CC1PAT                                    :F(X1KZ
)@@G@@-2A)S(C1)   @[@@@@*     @#@@@@*  MAX2 <= MIN1.  @[@@@@*     @[@@@@X2-1  LA
)@@G@@@E@@@@   IDENT(TYPE2,'F')  EQ(MAX2,MIN1)               :S(OLAP)   @F@@@@LB
)@@G@@   IDENT(TYPE2,'A')  IDENT(TYPE1,'A')  EQ(MAX2,MIN1)  :S(OLAP)    @#@@@@LC
)@@G@@X2-1A OUT  =  C2  @#@@@@   OUTPUT  =  C2  @E@@@@   C2  =  IN2           LD
)@@G@@                         :F(EOF2)   @F@@@@   C2  CC2PAT                 LE
)@@G@@                   :F(X2-1A)S(C2)   @[@@@@*     @[@@@@*     @^@@@@*  ENDLF
)@@G@@-OF-FILE LABELS:  @[@@@@*     @[@@@@*     @#@@@@EOF1  OUT  =  C2  @#@@@@LG
)@@G@@   OUTPUT  =  C2  @F@@@@EOF1A C2  =  IN2                                LH
)@@G@@ :S(EOF1)F(E)     @[@@@@*     @#@@@@EOF2  OUT  =  C1  @#@@@@   OUTPUT  =LI
)@@G@@  C1  @E@@@@   C1  =  IN1                                    :S(EOF2)   LJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @^@@@@E  ENDFILE(OUTUNIT)     @[@@@@*     @[@@@@END   ___@@@LK
)@@G@@*  FROM UNIT 2, AND COPY THEM IF PRESENT. @[@@@@*     @]@@@@INITCC2     LL
)@@G@@@E@@@@   C2  CC2PAT     *[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@* INDEX-D ********************LM
)@@G@@******************************************@G@@@@* INDEX IS A SNOBOL4 PROLN
)@@G@@GRAM THAT READS IN A DECK CONTAINING AN INDEX   @F@@@@* IN AN EASY-TO-PULO
)@@G@@NCH FORM, AND OUTPUTS IT ALPHABETIZED AND IN A  @#@@@@* STANDARD FORMAT.LP
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @G@@@@* A CARD IN THE INPUT DECK CONTAINS FOUR THINGS:  AN ILQ
)@@G@@NDENTATION THAT   @G@@@@* CONSISTS OF A NUMBER OF BLANKS, AN 'ITEM' IN TLR
)@@G@@HE INDEX, A DELIMITER   @G@@@@* (ONE CHARACTER), AND THE 'LOCATION' OF TLS
)@@G@@HE ITEM IN THE TEXT BEING     @G@@@@* INDEXED.  THE ITEM AND LOCATION FILT
)@@G@@ELDS CAN BE ANY STRINGS THAT DON'T  @G@@@@* CONTAIN THE DELIMITER.  FOR LU
)@@G@@EXAMPLE, WITH A DELIMITER OF ':' (THE     @G@@@@* DEFAULT DELIMITER--THELV
)@@G@@ USER CAN SPECIFY A DIFFERENT ONE IF HE WANTS   @D@@@@* TO), A SMALL EXALW
)@@G@@MPLE OF AN INPUT DECK MIGHT BE:     @[@@@[*     @^@@@@*     TIME LIMIT:4LX
)@@G@@.1.1  @]@@@@*     DATA  @^@@@@*         SHARED:6.2    @^@@@@*         FILY
)@@G@@LES:6.2     @A@@@@*         TYPES--SEE DATA TYPES     @^@@@@*     OPERATLZ
)@@G@@ORS:4.2.2   @ @@@@*         AVAILABLE:4.2.2.2   @^@@@@*         NAME ('.MA
)@@G@@'):4.2@ @@@@*         DEFINING:4.2.2.1    @^@@@@*     FORMATS:1.3.1     MB
)@@G@@@[@@@@*     @G@@@[* IN THE FIRST CARD, 'TIME LIMIT' IS THE ITEM; '4.1.1'MC
)@@G@@ THE LOCATION.    @G@@@@* NOTE THAT THE DELIMITER AND LOCATION FIELDS MAMD
)@@G@@Y BE OMITTED, IN WHICH  @G@@@@* CASE THEY WILL JUST BE IGNORED BY THE PRME
)@@G@@OGRAM.  THE GROUPS OF ITEMS   @G@@@@* WITH THE SAME INDENTATION WILL BE MF
)@@G@@ALPHABETIZED IN THE OBVIOUS WAY,    @F@@@@* KEEPING GROUPS TOGETHER WITHMG
)@@G@@ THEIR PRECEDING ITEM FOR WHICH THEY@F@@@@* ARE A 'SUB-GROUP'.  AFTER THMH
)@@G@@E ALPHABETIZATION, THE ABOVE EXAMPLE@#@@@@* WOULD LOOK LIKE:@[@@@[*     MI
)@@G@@@]@@@@*     DATA  @^@@@@*         FILES:6.2     @^@@@@*         SHARED:6MJ
)@@G@@.2    @A@@@@*         TYPES--SEE DATA TYPES     @^@@@@*     FORMATS:1.3.MK
)@@G@@1     @^@@@@*     OPERATORS:4.2.2   @ @@@@*         AVAILABLE:4.2.2.2   ML
)@@G@@@ @@@@*         DEFINING:4.2.2.1    @^@@@@*         NAME ('.'):4.2@^@@@@MM
)@@G@@*     TIME LIMIT:4.1.1  @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* THE PROGRAM WILL ACCEPT ANY MN
)@@G@@NUMBER OF LEVELS OF INDENTATION, LIMITED  @G@@@@* ONLY BY WHAT CAN BE FIMO
)@@G@@T INTO AN 80-COLUMN CARD.  IF CHARACTERS OTHER  @G@@@@* THAN LETTERS OCCMP
)@@G@@UR IN AN ITEM, THEY WILL BE ALPHABETIZED ACCORDING    @F@@@@* TO THE NUMMQ
)@@G@@ERIC ORDER OF THE CHARACTER SET.  THIS CAN BE EASILY  @F@@@@* DETERMINEDMR
)@@G@@ BY RUNNING A SNOBOL PROGRAM THAT PRINTS THE VALUE    @ @@@@* OF THE KEYMS
)@@G@@WORD &ALPHABET.   @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* AFTER ALPHABETIZING THE INDEX, IT MT
)@@G@@IS OUTPUT TO THE LINE PRINTER AND   @G@@@@* TO ANOTHER FILE ASSIGNABLE BMU
)@@G@@Y THE USER.  EACH LINE IS REFORMATTED     @G@@@@* SO THAT THE LOCATION FMV
)@@G@@IELD IS RIGHT-JUSTIFIED TO A CERTAIN COLUMN     @F@@@@* (SPECIFIABLE BY MW
)@@G@@THE USER), AND A STRING OF PERIODS IS INSERTED  @F@@@@* BEFORE IT.  TO EMX
)@@G@@XPRESS THIS IN A DIFFERENT WAY, THE DELIMITER IN@G@@@@* THE ORIGINAL CARMY
)@@G@@D IS EXPANDED INTO A STRING OF PERIODS LONG ENOUGH    @G@@@@* TO MAKE THMZ
)@@G@@E ENTIRE OUTPUT STRING (INDENTATION, ITEM, PERIODS, AND     @G@@@@* LOCANA
)@@G@@TION) A CERTAIN PRE-DETERMINED LENGTH.  THE ABOVE EXAMPLE WOULD   @#@@@@NB
)@@G@@* BE OUTPUT AS:   @[@@@[*     @]@@@@*     DATA  @B@@@@*         FILES . NC
)@@G@@. . . . . . . . . .6.2  @B@@@@*         SHARED. . . . . . . . . . .6.2  ND
)@@G@@@A@@@@*         TYPES--SEE DATA TYPES     @B@@@@*     FORMATS . . . . . NE
)@@G@@. . . . . .1.3.1  @B@@@@*     OPERATORS . . . . . . . . . .4.2.2  @B@@@@NF
)@@G@@*         AVAILABLE . . . . . . .4.2.2.2  @B@@@@*         DEFINING. . . NG
)@@G@@. . . . .4.2.2.1  @B@@@@*         NAME ('.'). . . . . . . . .4.2  @B@@@@NH
)@@G@@*     TIME LIMIT. . . . . . . . . .4.1.1  @[@@@@*     @F@@@@* THERE ARE NI
)@@G@@FOUR VARIABLES THAT A USER MAY WANT TO INITIALIZE:    @G@@@@*     DELIMINJ
)@@G@@TER IS A STRING OF CHARACTERS (1 OR MORE) THAT ARE TO BE    @F@@@@*     NK
)@@G@@    INTERPRETED AS DELIMITERS BETWEEN THE ITEM AND LOCATION @C@@@@*     NL
)@@G@@    FIELDS.  THE DEFAULT VALUE IS ':'.    @G@@@@*     WIDTH IS THE NUMBENM
)@@G@@R OF COLUMNS TO USE FOR OUTPUT.  ITS DEFAULT    @^@[@@*         VALUE ISNN
)@@G@@ 50.  @G@@@[*         VALUE IS 50.  IF A LINE REQUIRES MORE THAN THIS, ANO
)@@G@@ WARNING    @G@@@[*         MESSAGE WILL APPEAR IN THE LISTING AND NO CANP
)@@G@@RD WILL BE SENT   @ @@@[*         TO UNITO (Q.V.).    @F@@@@*     UNITI NQ
)@@G@@IS THE INPUT UNIT.  DEFAULT IS STANDARD INPUT (5).    @F@@@@*     UNITO NR
)@@G@@IS THE OUTPUT UNIT.  DEFAULT IS STANDARD PUNCH (1).   @[@@@@*     @F@@[]NS
)@@G@@* AS SHOWN IN THE ABOVE EXAMPLE, A LINE THAT DOESN'T CONTAIN THE  @F@@[]NT
)@@G@@* DELIMITER WILL BE OUTPUT JUST AS IT WAS IN THE INPUT DECK.  THIS@G@@[]NU
)@@G@@* MEANS THAT THE PROGRAM CAN BE USED ANOTHER WAY:  IF THE DELIMITER     NV
)@@G@@@F@@[]* IS A CHARACTER THAT DOESN'T OCCUR IN THE DECK, THE DECK WILL BE NW
)@@G@@@F@@[]* OUTPUT IN THE FORM INDICATED BY THE SECOND DECK ABOVE.  THAT IS,NX
)@@G@@@F@@[]* YOU CAN GET YOUR DECK SORTED WITHOUT RE-FORMATTING BY SPECIFYINGNY
)@@G@@@^@@[]* A 'WRONG' DELIMITER.  @[@@[]*     @[@@@@*     @F@@@@* AS AN EXAMNZ
)@@G@@PLE OF THE USE OF THIS PROGRAM, SUPPOSE THE INPUT DECK@G@@@@* IS ON UNITOA
)@@G@@ 15, WE WANT UNIT 23 AS OUTPUT UNIT, '/' IS USED AS THE     @F@@@@* DELIOB
)@@G@@MITER, AND WE WOULD LIKE A 60-COLUMN-WIDE INDEX.  THIS COULD@#@@@@* BE DOC
)@@G@@ONE BY:     @#@@@@*     @SNOBOL     @ @@@@*         DELIMITER  =  '/'   OD
)@@G@@@^@@@@*         WIDTH  =  60  @^@@@@*         UNITI  =  15  @^@@@@*     OE
)@@G@@    UNITO  =  23  @ @]@@*     ADD   SNOBOL*LIB.INDEX  @ @@[]*     @ADD  OF
)@@G@@SNOBOL*LIB.INDEX  @[[@@@*     @G@@@@* FOR ANOTHER EXAMPLE, SUPPOSE WE HAOG
)@@G@@VE A DECK OF CARDS USING ':' AS     @G@@@@* DELIMITER, AND WANT 40-COLUMOH
)@@G@@N PUNCHED OUTPUT.  THIS COULD BE DONE BY: @#@@@@*     @SNOBOL     @^@@@@OI
)@@G@@*         WIDTH  =  40  @ @@@@*     @ADD  SNOBOL*LIB.INDEX  @^@@@@*     OJ
)@@G@@    **DATA DECK** @[@@@@*     @G@@@@* AS INDICATED BY THESE EXAMPLES, THOK
)@@G@@E PROGRAM CONTAINS AN END CARD, SO  @G@@@@* YOU SHOULDN'T INCLUDE ONE OFOL
)@@G@@ YOUR OWN.  FOR AN EXAMPLE OF A LARGE     @G@@@@* INDEX PROCESSED BY THIOM
